                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d436">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/4308: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-04-26T17:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 26, 1922—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 26—9:28 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>172. Seventh paragraph my 164 of April 24. Admiral Strauss<note n="28"
                        xml:id="d436fn28">Rear Admiral Joseph Strauss, Commander in Chief, U. S.
                        Asiatic Fleet.</note> sailed from Manila yesterday on <hi rend="italic"
                        >Huron</hi> for Chinwangtao. U.S.S. <hi rend="italic">Albany</hi> is
                    expected at same port tomorrow noon bringing 175 officers and men to reinforce
                    Legation Guard. This will bring strength of guard up to 525.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Schurman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
